					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">But then PC monitors tend to lack SD inputs at all. Some of those filters are needed to hide the limits of SD inputs. I've noticed that when I run a PC's VGA out to my Vizio LCD TV's VGA in, I don't get near as much lag or filter artifacting.<br /><br />In addition, PC monitors are sized for one person on a desk, not two to four people in a living room, so they're a bit harder to use with offline multiplayer games. Good luck with your Four Score. On the other hand, 1080p monitors for desktop PCs are already as tall as the 48 cm (19 inch)-diagonal 4:3 CRT SDTVs that used to be common as secondary bedroom TVs.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

